{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/punc/punc-01350/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PUNC-01350"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:13:50"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Punch-Drunk Love"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, crane, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["high key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man bumps into a glass door before opening it and stepping through."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PUNC-01350","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PUNC-01350"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1/00a67d3a-a90f-4391-a4b1-857e80ea9f13","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-15T18:05:47.360Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In his nervous state Barry forgets to open his door and runs into it. Despite his tendency to break doors, as he will soon do at his sister's house, he struggles with his own. As the office and warehouse represent a manifestation of his internal state, his confusion here reveals his inability to change his way of life.</p><p>One of the primary influences on <em>Punch-Drunk Love</em> were the films of Jacques Tati. In <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-600\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oS6pwQqSY70\">this scene</a> from <em>Playtime</em> (1967), Tati's hero, Monsieur Hulot, struggles with a door in a similar way.</p><p>With this in mind, Adam Sandler's casting in this role is not surprising, as the two actors have many connections: both have Russian ancestry, both became famous for physical comedy performances in episodic shows (Tati miming in <em>Impressions Sportives</em> and Sandler in the TV sketch comedy show <em>Saturday Night Live</em>), and both later transitioned to cinema and created their own production companies.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01350/canvas/1#xywh=709,136,564,538"}]}]}]}